freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: I caught a bad cold the day after I got the vaccine and was sick with it but better today. I was worried i was sick from the vaccine but Im sure it was just a cold because Im better today after fainting and falling yesterday. Ive never fallen ever before yesterday.  I have som congestion still today but not as bad. Yesterday was the worst. No fever, just a lot of congestion just odd timing but not vaccine related I dont think. Yesterday was my worst day since Sunday, the day after my first Pfizer shot.
I fainted this morning trying to get to my chair and I went down on the floor in front of the chair.

I had a bad cold hit me the day after my shot and Sunday-Tuesday I felt terrible with lots of congestion down the back of my throat with coughing.  I took Airborne, Coricidin, Thera Flu, RX Benzoate 200mg, Nasal Spray and used Lemon cough drops.  On Tuesday afternoon I got overheated and fainted hitting my  head and shoulder trying to get to my chair.  I backed off on too many cold remedies and started feeling better Wednesday.  Im at the end of the cold now with some congestion in the back of my throat and feeling almost normal. I dont believe it had anything to do with the vaccine but fluke timing coming down with a cold the next day after the shot.
I had two extreme back surgeries 3 years ago and I feel slight discomfort in that area.
